@startuml MagicLinkSSO-Overview

title Magic Link SSO Overview

left to right direction

actor User
rectangle "Protected App\nor Private Resource" as App
rectangle "Magic Link SSO" as SSO
rectangle "Email Inbox" as Email

User --> App : 1. Open protected page
App --> SSO : 2. Start sign-in flow\n(framework integration or Gate)
SSO --> Email : 3. Send magic link
Email --> User : 4. Deliver sign-in link
User --> App : 5. Return with verified session
App --> User : 6. Serve protected page,\nAPI, or asset

note bottom of App
The protected target can be:
- a framework app with direct integration
- a private upstream behind Magic Link SSO Gate
end note

@enduml
